Pension assets in Nigeria grew by N29 billion from the N8.74 billion recorded a+t the end of January to N9.03 as at the end of March, 2019. Data from the National Pension Commission (PenCom) showed that 11,000 Retirement Savings Accounts (RSAs) holders joined the scheme within the period under review. Membership of the Contributory pension Scheme (CPS) soared from 8.46 million RSAs holders in January to 8.57 million in March. RSAs holders from the public sector grew from 2.35 million in January to 2.37 million by March while private sector RSA holders jumped from 3.62 million to 3.68 million RSAs same period. Pension fund asset hits  N2.4 Trn - DG Pension fund infrastructure investments rose by 600% in 20 months - Dahir-Umar CPS: FG paid N98.28bn to 289,126 disengaged workers Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin